The paper discusses the use of machine learning and wearable sensors to study cognitive development, specifically language development in infants. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of Computation and Language (cs.CL). The paper also discusses the use of artificial intelligence and the need to move from toy problems to full complexity, which suggests that it could also belong to the sub-category of Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the need for privacy-preserving repositories of home data, which suggests that it could belong to the sub-category of Computers and Society (cs.CY). Finally, the paper mentions the use of specific tests to benchmark humans and machines at different linguistic levels, which suggests that it could also belong to the sub-category of Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV).
